Try faceting out data with multiple categories. You can treat groups as columns or rows as well as hue color within a graph. Graphs should communicate information quickly and with clarity. Too many colors or lines can sometimes be as bad as too few colors or lines.
Swarm plots should be avoided for larger datasets imo. Not very descriptive.
Check your max and min settings on your plot function. Too high and you'll wash out your heat map, too low and you'll make it not very informative
Check your data types. If you're working in pandas, just do a df.dtypes to see if you have numeric data or not.
